The paper proposes a method for fitting and segmenting multi-structural data, which is a common problem in computer vision and graphics. The paper uses a hypergraph model to represent the complex relationships between model hypotheses and data points, which is a common technique in computer vision and machine learning. The paper also develops a robust hypergraph partition algorithm to detect sub-hypergraphs for model fitting, which is a common technique in computer science and optimization. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
